The '''Edinburgh Annuale''' is a visual art festival involving [[Edinburgh]] [[art gallery|galleries]] and art projects, especially ones that promote local activity in the [[visual arts]]. The Edinburgh Annuale exists to promote grassroots visual arts operations in the city.

The Annuale is co-ordinated by Edinburgh Artist Run Initiative [http://www.embassygallery.org The Embassy] with a programme including publication launches, [[Live Art (art form)|live events]] and [[Art exhibition|exhibitions]]. The first Edinburgh Annuale took place in August 2004 and included exhibitions at The Embassy, Wuthering Heights, Magnifitat, The Forest Cafe and Aurora Projects. The festival has grown to include many more events and exhibitions and has some financial support from the [[Scottish Arts Council]] amongst others.

